                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/7161.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-15T22:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1913—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>183. If the Department can do anything to aid Mexico in negotiating a loan at
                    this moment, such action would possibly result in restoring peace and in
                    enabling this Government to maintain itself, as the great absorbing question is
                    the economic one. I am not prepared to suggest how such aid could be rendered as
                    I am not in possession of the Department’s views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
